Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
findLefEquivalentCells(25.10)                    findLefEquivalentCells(25.10)

Name
       findLefEquivalentCells  -  Provides support to debug certain cells that
       may be non-equivalent without detailed analysis of the LEF

Syntax
       findLefEquivalentCells

       [-help]

        -cells <string>

        [-outfile <filename>]

       Provides support to debug certain  cells  that  may  be  non-equivalent
       without  detailed  analysis  of the LEF. For example, if two cells have
       the same function and size they still may not be LEF equivalent.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each findLefEquivalentCells parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command: man findLefEquivalentCells

       -cells <string>
              Specifies the cell names. You can also use wildcards or  specify
              individual cells.

       -outfile <filename>
              Specifies  the  output  file  name  for reporting LEF equivalent
              cells. All the equivalent and non-equivalent cells are saved  in
              the output file.

Examples
              * The  following example command reports equivalence information
                on all cells and outputs to a file:

                findLefEquivalentCells -cells * -outFile equivalency_file.txt

              * To report equivalence information  on  a  specific  cell,  say
                SCBUF1X, you can use the following command:

                findLefEquivalentCells -cells SCBUF1X

              * To report equivalence information on all cells that begin with
                SCBUF, you can use the following command:

                findLefEquivalentCells -cells SCBUF*

